## Proposed Changes

### Change 1: Fix Dashboard Position in Sidebar

**Issue:** Dashboard should be fixed at top, not draggable.

**Files to Modify:**
1. `src/components/Sidebar.tsx` - Extract Dashboard from navigation array
2. `src/stores/useSidebarNavStore.ts` - Update default order (remove '/')

**Implementation:**

**Step 1:** Split navigation into fixed + draggable items in `Sidebar.tsx`:

```typescript
// Lines 19-24: Split navigation into two arrays
const fixedNavigation: NavItem[] = [
  { icon: '🏠', label: 'Dashboard', path: '/', shortcut: 'D', hasSettings: true },
];

const draggableNavigation: NavItem[] = [
  { icon: '📝', label: 'Notes', path: '/notes', shortcut: 'N', hasSettings: false },
  { icon: '📅', label: 'Planning', path: '/planning', shortcut: 'P', hasSettings: false },
  { icon: '✓', label: 'Tasks', path: '/tasks', shortcut: 'T', hasSettings: false },
];
```

**Step 2:** Render Dashboard as fixed item (non-sortable):

```typescript
{/* Navigation Items */}
<nav className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto py-4">
  <ul className="space-y-1 px-2">
    {/* Fixed Navigation (Dashboard - not draggable) */}
    {fixedNavigation.map((item) => (
      <li key={item.path}>
        <Link to={item.path} className={/* same styling */}>
          {/* Same content as SortableNavItem but NO drag handle */}
        </Link>
      </li>
    ))}

    {/* Draggable Navigation (Notes, Planning, Tasks) */}
    <DndContext sensors={sensors} collisionDetection={closestCenter} onDragEnd={handleDragEnd}>
      <SortableContext items={navOrder} strategy={verticalListSortingStrategy}>
        {sortedDraggableNavigation.map((item) => (
          <SortableNavItem /* ... */ />
        ))}
      </SortableContext>
    </DndContext>
  </ul>
</nav>
```

**Step 3:** Update `useSidebarNavStore.ts` default order:

```typescript
// Remove '/' from default order (Dashboard not in drag list)
const DEFAULT_NAV_ORDER = ['/notes', '/planning', '/tasks'];
```

**Step 4:** Update sorting logic to only sort draggable items:

```typescript
// Filter out Dashboard before sorting
const sortedDraggableNavigation = draggableNavigation.sort((a, b) => {
  const aIndex = navOrder.indexOf(a.path);
  const bIndex = navOrder.indexOf(b.path);
  return (aIndex === -1 ? 999 : aIndex) - (bIndex === -1 ? 999 : bIndex);
});
```

**Estimated Time:** 1 hour

